2011-02-21|2011-02-27.description:
Julie and Annie share the same body and must act as one to stop the Phi Collider. Once inside the top secret facility they must fight their way through indomitable security and find the man responsible for it all, Professor Foster. Only Foster can stop the machine that threatens the world, and only Foster holds the key to setting Annie free!

In D.C. Stephanie (baring a Parker Girl tattoo on her right thigh) is showering when she senses something she grabs a gun but Tambi throws her to the floor. Tambi asks her for the location of the Phi collider and how to get in.

In Alaska Ivy reads up on Cain and reads the tales that say that when Cain is killed, as the son of Adam, it will mark the 7 day countdown to the unmaking of earth. The last day by that reckoning would be the next one, the day of the colliders testing.

Tambi phones in the location of the colider to Ivy, it will be at 6:18 that evening and Ivy notes the biblical relevance. Ivy is now little more than a 12 year old and tantrums when she finds Dillon and Julie possibly having sex.

At the collider the generals arrive and they confirm that its under tested but with the Chinese tests coming they have no choice.

2011-03-14|2011-03-20.description:
Wes Craven's Scream became the biggest horror franchise of the '90s and helped usher in the 'teen slasher' craze that took over Hollywood. HorrorHound looks back at the Scream franchise as Craven prepares to unleash his latest installment, the long-anticipated Scream 4.

Plus, a look at the latest reboot of The Thing and a peek at the history of the 'Alien Invasion' genre.

  • The Walking Dead
  • Movie Posters: Sex, Horror And Torture. Females In Chains
  • The Ghouligans!
2011-03-14|2011-03-20.name: HorrorHound #28

2011-04-18|2011-04-24.description:
The ultimate guide to the adventures of the Doctorâs most enduring companion!

Written and researched by Andrew Pixley.

Sarah Jane Smith â journalist, mother and friend of the Doctor's! Over the last few years, Sarah Jane has been responsible for saving the Earth on countless occasions. With the help of her robot dog K9, her computer Mr Smith, her son Luke, and her young friends Clyde Langer and Rani Chandra, sheâs faced a multitude of menaces including Judoon, Shansheeth, Slitheen, the Trickster â¦ even the Mona Lisa! And twice recently, she was visited by the last of the Time Lords, in remarkable adventures that would test her courage to the limit.

Now, Doctor Who Magazine takes you behind the scenes of The Sarah Jane Adventures with an in-depth episode guide â including original storylines, deleted scenes, media appearances, ratings information and thousands of facts about the day-to-day life of the making of the award-winning programme - all illustrated with gorgeous, never-before-seen photographs. This collector's edition examines Prisoner of the Judoon, The Mad Woman in the Attic, The Wedding of Sarah Jane Smith, The Eternity Trap, Mona Lisa's Revenge, The Gift, The Nightmare Man, The Vault of Secrets, Death of the Doctor, The Empty Planet, Lost in Time and Goodbye, Sarah Jane Smith, as well as The Alien Files, the specially-made trailers and more!

Get ready to discover a whole universe of adventure â right here on your doorstep!
2011-04-18|2011-04-24.name: The Sarah Jane Companion: Volume Two

2011-05-09|2011-05-15.description:
With Starro the Conqueror on the verge of complete victory, our rebel fighters Lobo, Vril Dox, Adam Strange, Starfire and the gang pull out all the stops in this series' bloody conclusion!

Starro has used his Starro spores to take over most of New Rann. He has Vril dox under his control, and his only real restince is Blackfire, Starfire, Captain Comet, and Adam Strange, who he seems to be able to handle until Lyrl releases his secret weapon, a suped up Tribulus, with the new abilty to short circuit Starro's spores.

Even thoughTribulus is destroying the spores outside Starro and Vril able to keep the REBEL heroes in a cornar. As a last ditch effort Adam is able to turn on Vril's homing devise for Tribulus and bring the Starro killer to them.

Meanwhile back on Psion Smite and Lobo have become friends and Smite explains there is a jump gate on Psion and that the stranded REBEL team can get to New Rann with it. After the team leaves for New Rann they tell the now freed Vril to push Starro threw the gate, where Lobo and Smite are waiting for him.

One Week Later. New Rann seems at peace, Lyrl has escaped again and Vril and Blackfire have picked up their relationship where it left off.
2011-05-09|2011-05-15.name: Starstruck, Conclusion

2011-05-09|2011-05-15.description: The diabolical schemes of Dr Phibes escalate to fiendishly greater heights as the clock ticks towards a new millennium! Murders are one thing, museums quite another, but together they might just hold the clues to mysteries older than time to prevent the unfathomable conjuring of dark magic in this twilight age. For Dr. Anton Phibes, this is all about love and he will do anything to see his dreams come true. Absolutely anything!
2011-05-09|2011-05-15.name: The Return of Dr. Phibes

2011-05-16|2011-05-22.description: The Freedom Fighters have fallen! Now the only one left to save this dark world is Silver the Hedgehog! It's psychic power versus chaos power as our hero from the future goes all-out against the terrifying Enerjak! Don't miss the cataclysmic conclusion to the Silver Saga!
2011-05-16|2011-05-22.name: Fractured Mirror, Part Four

2011-07-25|2011-07-31.description: The New Mutants have found X-Man, but in the clutches of Sugar Man! What is Sugar Man doing with Nate? And what is Nate going to do to Sugar Man once the New Mutants get him freed. It's not every day you get an Omega Level Mutant angry...

Over two years in the making, see how everything ends after last month's shocking conclusion. What will happen to Nick Fury? Who lives? Who dies? What is the stunning new direction for the remnants of S.H.I.E.L.D. in the Marvel Universe? Find out in Secret Warriors #28 -- it's "Wheels within Wheels," Part 5: FINALE
2011-07-25|2011-07-31.name: The One Man

2011-08-01|2011-08-07.description: Haven't picked up Irredeemable yet? Now is your chance as a brand new arc is set to begin in this multiple Eisner and Harvey Award-nominated series. The Plutonian has gone from a Mad God wreaking havoc on the world to a captured denizen of an intergalactic insane asylum. Legendary comic writer Mark Waid continues this rollercoaster of a saga with an issue that's new reader friendly and sure to shock longtime fans. Don't dare miss this epic superhero comic that is redefining the genre!

2011-08-08|2011-08-14.description: While the cabal continue their seemingly motiveless murder spree, Tom researches his father's journals to uncover the secret connections between Wilson Taylor and his deadliest enemy, Pullman â as well as a hint at an eighty-year-old atrocity that could be a clue to Tom's own nature and origins!
2011-08-08|2011-08-14.name: On to Genesis, Part Two of Four
